
========================
jose - 1.5 Release Notes
========================

peteschaefer.github.io/jose
hrimfaxi.bitbucket.io/jose


==================
Files for Download
==================

* jose-152-windows.zip              zip archive for Windows
* jose-152-linux.zip                zip archive for Linux with Intel processors
* jose-152-mac-intel.zip            zip archive for macOS with Intel processors
* jose-152-mac-arm.zip              zip archive for macOS wiht Apple Silicon (ARM 64) processors

* jose-153-patch.zip                patch to be applied on top of 1.5.2

* database-10k.jose                Database containing 10.000 grandmaster games
* database-500k.jose               Database containing more than 500.000 games
* database-1700k.jose              Database containing more than 1.7 million games



============
Requirements
============

* Operating Systems: 
   - Windows 98 or later
   - Linux with Intel processors
   - macOS with Intel or Apple Silicon (since?)

==================
Patch Installation
==================

* Patches are light-weight zip packages that can be installed on-top-of a full installation
* just unzip and replace the old files
* patches are platform-agnostic and cumulative (i.e. you need only the latest patch)


====================
Windows Installation
====================

* Unpack the zip file into a directory of your choice

* You can start jose by double-clicking "jose.exe"
  or you can start it from the command line with
     java -jar jose.jar

* jose includes a number of TrueType fonts for displaying chess figurines.
  If you like to use these fonts with other applications,
  copy them from jose\fonts to C:\Windows\Fonts


==================
Linux Installation
==================

* Unpack the zip file into a directory of your choice, e.g.
     unzip -D /usr/share/games jose-142-linux.zip

* Start jose with the script "jose.sh"
  or you can start it from the command line with
     java -jar jose.jar

* if display looks too small on hi-dpi screens,
  adjust the UI scaling factor. See jose.sh

======================
3D System Requirements
======================

* WINDOWS
    - Windows 2000 or Windows XP
    - OpenGL 1.1

* LINUX
  - Graphics adapter with driver that supports the GLX extension:
    GLX 1.3 or later and OpenGL 1.2 or later

* MACOS
  - ?

=====================================
Installing the Sample Games Databases
=====================================

* choose Open... from the File menu
* select a database archive file (*.jose)
* opening an archive file may take some time.
  However, the import need only be run once.
  After the archive has been copied into your personal
  database, it will be available immediately.

* when upgrading from an older version, just move the database directory
  to the new installation
* it is recommended to make regular backups of the database directory
* if, for some reason, the database becomes corrupted, run
  Help / Repair Database...
  the repair tool can fix most cases without losing valuable data

========================
Setting up Chess Engines
========================

* Stockfish and Leela Chess Zero (Lc0) are readily bundled
* depending on your available hardware, you may want to upgrade
  the Leela installation with a customized executable, and with neural nets
* refer to Lc0 instructions at lc0.org

=========================  
Removing the Installation
=========================

* remove the installation folder
* remove .jose.user.preferences from your home directory

=========================

Have fun,
Peter




